# =========================================
# Environment Setup Guide
# =========================================
#
# This project uses Vite's multi-file env system to separate local dev from production:
#
#   .env.development     — Local Supabase URL + anon key (committed, not secret)
#   .env.local           — Shared secrets: Google OAuth, RapidAPI key (git-ignored)
#   Vercel dashboard     — Production Supabase URL + anon key (never in files)
#
# `npm run dev`   → loads .env.development + .env.local (hits LOCAL Supabase)
# `npm run build` → loads .env.local only (on Vercel, env vars come from dashboard)
#
# IMPORTANT: Do NOT put VITE_SUPABASE_URL or VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY in .env.local!
# That would override .env.development and point local dev at production.
#
# To pull production data into your local Supabase:
#   npm run pull-prod-data
#
# =========================================

# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in real values:

# =========================================
# Google OAuth (for "Sign in with Google")
# =========================================
# To enable Google OAuth:
#
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select existing one
# 3. Go to "APIs & Services" > "Credentials"
# 4. Click "Create Credentials" > "OAuth client ID"
# 5. Configure the OAuth consent screen first if prompted
# 6. Select "Web application" as application type
# 7. Add authorized redirect URIs:
#    - For local: http://localhost:54321/auth/v1/callback
#    - For production: https://your-domain.com/auth/callback
# 8. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret below
#
# NOTE: These go in supabase/config.toml for local development
# or in Supabase Dashboard > Authentication > Providers for production

GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret

# =========================================
# ExerciseDB API (optional, for exercise GIFs)
# =========================================
VITE_RAPIDAPI_KEY=your-rapidapi-key
